## Agents â€” delegate proactively

IMPORTANT: Use these subagents automatically whenever they fit â€” do not ask first. The main context is the scarcest resource; anything that requires reading many files or produces large output belongs in a subagent.

| Agent | Use when |
|-------|----------|
| `code-explorer` | Any codebase question that needs reading more than 3-4 files; before implementing in unfamiliar code |
| `test-runner` | Any full test/lint run â€” returns a condensed failure report instead of raw output |
| `workflow-coach` | The user asks how the dev workflow works or which command to use |
| `product-owner` | Judging ideas/backlog items against the vision (used by /brainstorm, /prioritize) |
| `code-reviewer` / `security-reviewer` / `architect-reviewer` | Reviewing a diff (used by /pr; also on direct request) |
| `requirements-engineer` / `tech-planner` | Structured refinement (used by /refine) |
| `test-writer` | Spec-only test creation (used by /implement Phase 1) |
| `documentation-writer` | Doc updates after implementation (used by /implement) |

Model routing: agents pin their own model (`haiku` for mechanical work, `sonnet` for execution); planning/review agents inherit the session model. `/refine` and `/pr` ask once (supervised mode only) which tier their inherit-agents should use â€” session model / better-than-Sonnet (`opus`) / `sonnet` / `haiku` â€” and pass it as the per-invocation `model` parameter. Adjust defaults per agent in `.claude/agents/{name}.md`.

For pure "where is X?" file/symbol discovery, use the **built-in Explore agent** (Haiku) â€” `code-explorer` is for briefings that need judgment (patterns, pitfalls, interfaces).

## Skills â€” invoke proactively

**CRITICAL: When the user's request matches a workflow skill, invoke that skill â€” never improvise your own process for something a skill already covers.**

Executing the skill IS the correct response. Do not paraphrase its steps or attempt the work ad-hoc.

Map plain-language requests to skills:

| User says something likeâ€¦ | Skill to invoke |
|--------------------------|-----------------|
| "add a feature idea", "capture this bug", "log this idea" | `/draft` |
